1
00:00:04,039 --> 00:00:06,868
The first principle to understand is

2
00:00:06,868 --> 00:00:15,717
that Madan, Eros, Cupid,
is creating moha, illusion,

3
00:00:15,717 --> 00:00:20,332
and that’s why the illusory world
is being driven by this principle,

4
00:00:20,563 --> 00:00:23,158
[Freud, Eros, and Kṛṣṇa]

5
00:00:23,158 --> 00:00:25,414
it’s what makes it spin.

6
00:00:25,953 --> 00:00:31,942
But here, Madan’s creating
moha for the jīva-souls.

7
00:00:31,942 --> 00:00:35,399
Eros is creating illusion
for everyone,

8
00:00:35,399 --> 00:00:39,808
it’s the driving principal
of material existence.

9
00:00:39,808 --> 00:00:46,721
Madan-mohan means, 
Kṛṣṇa is so beautiful,

10
00:00:46,722 --> 00:00:49,804
so seductively charming,

11
00:00:49,804 --> 00:00:56,540
that Kṛṣṇa is creating moha,
illusion for Madan.

12
00:00:56,540 --> 00:01:00,817
Kṛṣṇa is putting Eros
into illusion.

13
00:01:00,869 --> 00:01:06,024
Eros is being seduced
by the Kṛṣṇa conception.

14
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:09,794
So, as Guru Mahārāj will say
in regard to Mahāprabhu,

15
00:01:09,794 --> 00:01:13,442
“Koṭi-kāma-mūrcchitāṅghri-rūpa-rāsa-raṅgaraṁ”
(Premadhāma-deva-stotram: 2),

16
00:01:13,442 --> 00:01:18,213
cupids are fainting
to see the beauty,

17
00:01:19,505 --> 00:01:24,734
“Hiraṇyāṇāṁ lakṣmī-bharam abhibhavan
āṅgika-ruchā” (Prathama Chaitanyāṣṭaka: 4).

18
00:01:24,734 --> 00:01:29,603
Sometimes we use the expression
in it’s common usage,

19
00:01:29,603 --> 00:01:34,240
we’ll say someone
is painfully beautiful.

20
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:37,650
You look at them 
and they’re so beautiful

21
00:01:37,650 --> 00:01:43,096
that it’s some kind of
pleasant pain we experience.

22
00:01:43,096 --> 00:01:44,992
You can’t stop 
looking at them,

23
00:01:44,992 --> 00:01:47,536
you look away from them
and you want to look back,

24
00:01:47,536 --> 00:01:49,416
but if you look for too long,

25
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:52,988
they’re just painfully beautiful.

26
00:01:52,988 --> 00:01:57,285
That’s the type of beauty.

27
00:01:57,285 --> 00:02:03,833
When Śrīmati Rādhārāṇī’s heart
is enveloping Kṛṣṇa,

28
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:06,426
He looks so painfully beautiful

29
00:02:06,426 --> 00:02:09,324
that 10 million cupids
are swooning.

